    topic: "Dermatology",
    subtopic: "Ramsay Hunt syndrome",
    stem: `Jane, 53 years, presents to your GP practice with facial weakness, right ptosis, and drooling from the right corner of her mouth since this morning. She mentions a history of right ear pain a few days earlier. On examination, an erythematous vesicular rash is noted in the right ear canal. Which one of the following would be the most appropriate next step in management?`,
